 = 0.1 * 2 * 0.4 * 1.1309 = 0.090724\ny4 = 1.0607 + (0.063642 + 2 * 0.076575 + 2 * 0.07695 + 0.090724) / 6 = 1.1107\nx4 = 0.3 + 0.1 = 0.4\n\nSo, the approximation of y(0.4) using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method with a step size of h = 0.1 is y4 â‰ˆ 1.1107."
